Final 2023 Project: Reflect & Share   👨‍💻

Join Our End of Year Reflection and Celebration! #FacesOfALXSE #ALX_SE 🌟🥳

As the year draws to a close, we’re adding an exciting twist to our curriculum with our “Final 2023 Project: Reflect & Share”. This is a unique opportunity to conduct a comprehensive audit of your technical growth and your personal evolution, Especially as we ring in the new year.

Working as a Software Engineer requires taking a step back to look and reflect on the tasks you’ve completed and the products you’ve built. Now, Think of yourself as both the Engineer and the Product of this year’s journey. What have you learned, overcome, and achieved in 2023, both in your journey to becoming a software engineer and in life? We invite each one of you to participate in this reflective exercise.

Tasks

0. Reflect on Your Year

mandatory

Take a moment to reflect on your biggest win or lesson of 2023; it could be in the ALX software engineering program or something related. It could be a personal or professional achievement, a growth moment, or a valuable lesson learned.

Please share here a Google doc of your reflection - it must be at least 100 words.

Add URLs here:

  1. https://docs.google.com/document/d/1EQgxQIaNxhXRoZJvD0O3115RbysHiH-CmeT2XuQDmkM/edit?usp=drivesdk

1. Document & Share Your Reflection

mandatory

As a software engineer in training, you’re embarking on an exercise that mirrors what awaits in your professional future. When you land your first job or advance in your software engineering career, reflective exercises like this will be crucial in assessing your growth and impact. And remember, in this project, you are both the engineer and the product. “Facesofalxse” will serve as your Manager/Team Lead in this exercise, guiding you through this critical process of self-evaluation and learning.

Read all of the instructions before you get started.

Connect:

Your first task is to visit “facesofalxse” This is where you’ll find the specific instructions for your reflective journey - Pick one(1) of the platforms to access.

  • Twitter
  • LinkedIn
  • Facebook
  • TikTok

Reflect:

As you compile your milestones/experiences of 2023, consider how you’ve evolved not just in your technical skills but also as the ‘product’ of your learning and efforts. What have you developed and refined in yourself this year?

Follow:

  • Remember, “facesofalxse” is your Manager/Team Lead in this exercise, so following their instructions to the letter is crucial.
